    <stitle>PROPELLER SHAFT - LUBRICATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>LUBRICATION</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>Refer to GROUP 10 - LUBRICATION in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual for recommended lubricants and
                lubrication intervals.
            </para>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="1">
            <title>UNIVERSAL JOINT</title>
            <para>Add lubricant into the grease fitting until it appears at all journal cross bearing seals (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0600145">Figure 45</hotlnk>). This assures removal of dirt particles and other
                contaminants that may find their way into the bearings. Loosen any cups that fail to purge, or remove
                U-joint from yoke.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0600145" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0600145" filename="../figg06/G0600145.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                         scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 45. Add Lubricant into Grease Fitting</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
